The paper discusses a framework for distributed data structures, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses authentication and integrity mechanisms, which falls under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR). The use of directed acyclic graphs and hash references suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses network APIs and heterogeneous trust, which suggests that it may fall under the categories of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Systems and Control (cs.SY), respectively.
